## Per-run report template

Copy when running a full smoke session:

```
# Smoke run — YYYY-MM-DD

Tester: <handle>
Build: <commit SHA / image tag>
Environment: <local / staging>

## Results

| §  | Flow | Result | Notes |
| -- | ---- | ------ | ----- |
| §1 | <name> | pass / fail | <link to issue if filed> |
| §2 | <name> | pass / fail | |
```

## New-issue body template

Copy when filing a new issue from a failed smoke step:

```
**Discovered in:** smoke run YYYY-MM-DD, §N flow "<name>", step <M>.
**Build:** <SHA>.

**Steps to reproduce:**

1. ...
2. ...

**Expected:** <what the smoke playbook said would happen>
**Actual:** <what happened instead>
```
